    "extract": "The Central Securities Depository of Iran (CSDI) serves as the central registrar, depository, and clearinghouse for financial instruments traded on Iran’s capital market, as well as for physical market transactions in the Iran Energy Exchange. CSDI operates as an independent, self-regulatory organization (SRO) and provides pre-trade and post-trade services for Iran’s exchanges, including the Tehran Securities Exchange (TSE), Iran FaraBourse (IFB), Iran Energy Exchange (IRENEX), and Iran Mercantile Exchange (IME)."
